# RFC Implementation Completion Gate

When implementing from `specs/features/*/SPEC.md` or `specs/features/*/RFC.md`, do not treat work as complete until all of the following are true:

1. Every acceptance criterion is explicitly checked against the implementation.
2. Every acceptance criterion is covered by at least one test (unit, integration, component, or E2E).
3. If API error/status contracts are specified, each required error status has corresponding test coverage.
4. Any frontend mutation-path UX requirements (success/error display rules) are verified per call site, not assumed globally.

If any criterion lacks implementation or test coverage, report it as a gap and keep feature status as incomplete.
